Turkish Equity Movers: Koza, Petrol Ofisi, Turk Traktor Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-03-07T13:07:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/turkish-equity-movers-koza-petrol-ofisi-turk-traktor-move.html
  Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  lost 1,345.79, or 2.2 percent, to 59,767.04 at 2:53 p.m.
in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.    Koza Altin Isletmeleri AS (KOZAL)  , a gold producer, rose
70 kurus, or 3.6 percent, to 20.35 liras. Gold jumped to a
record $1,441.76 an ounce today as escalating violence in  Libya 
and concern inflation will accelerate boosted demand for the
metal as an alternative asset.  Petrol Ofisi (PTOFS TI), Turkey’s biggest fuel retailer,
added 8 kurus, or 1.1 percent, to 7.14 liras. A close at that
level would be the highest since Dec. 13. Oil advanced 2.2
percent to $106.76 a barrel in  New York  on concern unrest in the
Middle East will disrupt global energy supplies.  Turk Traktor & Ziraat Makineleri AS (TTRAK TI), a maker of
tractors and farm equipment, climbed 30 kurus, or 1.2 percent,
to 25.50 liras. The company said it would purchase assembly
services from Otokar Otomotiv & Savunma Sanayi AS (OTKAR TI), a
bus and military vehicle maker, to meet growing domestic demand
for tractors. Otokar increased 15 kurus, or 0.7 percent, to
22.20 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Ankara 
